# Schema Truth Guardrails

- Before changing any Supabase-backed route/service, verify live schema with MCP SQL (`information_schema`).
- If code needs missing tables/columns, create migration in `p11-platform/supabase/migrations`, then apply with MCP `apply_migration`.
- After schema changes, regenerate types with MCP `generate_typescript_types` and sync `p11-platform/apps/web/types/supabase.ts`.
- After syncing types, run `npm run schema:types:stamp` from `p11-platform/apps/web` to stamp the latest migration version into `types/supabase.ts`.
- Do not ship route code that references fields/tables missing from generated Supabase types.
- For side-effect routes (cron, outbound messaging, scoring, workflow actions), add/maintain tests and include trusted files in `p11-platform/apps/web/scripts/foundation-files.mjs`.
- Required validation from `p11-platform/apps/web`:
  - `npm run check:schema-types-sync`
  - `npm run check:schema-truth`
  - `npm run check:foundation`
- If checks fail, resolve schema/type drift first; do not bypass with broad `any`/unsafe casts.
